As the other reviews attest, this is a solid choice for a healthy, well made sit-down meal in Fidi, with nice options for vegans and vegetarians as well as kids, a spacious yet cozy environment, and decent restrooms. But the service is so disappointing! I do not fault our waitress at ALL, she was professional, smart and earnest. But the restaurant is woefully understaffed, with just too much distance to cover by too few servers, and I get the impression the manager must be trying to pinch pennies by forgoing positions like hosts (no greeter but a sign saying “seat yourself” for weekend brunch, in Manhattan, NYC? Who even does that??) and bussers (our one poor waitress essentially did it ALL, even moving heavy tables together to accommodate large parties).  Our experience was good for the most part as we weren’t in a hurry (and my daughter loved the pancakes!). But food was cold, we waited an awfully long time for our check, and our table was never cleaned when we were done eating. Again, not the fault of our server — clearly the management is trying to cut corners here and it shows. I would think LPQ Corporate would expect better for its guests AND staff, and hope that they get the message.

Wow. Wow. Wow.  When we visited the city we stopped in at Le Pain for breakfast/brunch two different times.   This is a great little place if you're looking for a creative menu with first-rate ingredients.  The staff does a good job helping explain and helping you imagine the meals as you ask.  They are attentive and responsive.  The two locations where we stopped both sported a modern/trendy design and seemed to be engineered to enjoy the local surroundings as well as other guests/patrons - evidenced by a 'community table' or two.  I had the best french toast I've ever had in my life here (may have been a special).  My wife got the Baker's Breakfast and my daughter got the Sunny Side Breakfast bowl - both were pleased beyond measure.  The coffee is superb as well!  So, if you're kicking around the city one weekend and looking for an environmentally and communally conscious restaurant that boasts an  unbelievably tasty menu and a friendly and knowledgeable staff (this is a rare combination), then this place is THE place for you!

So overall, I'm a fan of LPQ. It's my regular go-to spot for breakfast and coffee when I'm working out of my Wall Street office. The food usually is delicious and I love everything about their coffee. For breakfast, I recommend the avocado toast. I've had a few different variations of it from the smoked salmon to a ceviche style toast and I've loved them all. You get pretty big portions and it's filling. If you're looking for something lighter, try their parfaits. The only thing I find weird is that their coffee cups (when dining in) have no handles, which makes it difficult when I'm working and trying to one hand my coffee, but that's a small thing. The only reason I give this particular location a 3 because consistently, the serving staff has just been completely inattentive. Aside from initially taking your order and bringing your food, I've consistently had to get up and chase down my server for assistance or to even just get the check. It's annoying, particularly if I'm having a business meeting and I need something but have to continuously interrupt my conversation get up to flag down someone for help.
